  id: Cervicoscutular_muscle.R
  partName: Cervicoscutular muscle Right
  descriptionChunks:
  - The right cervicoscutular muscle Right is positioned within the superficial cervical
    region of the canine anatomy and connects skin structures around the neck and
    shoulder. Its primary function involves moving and tightening the skin in response
    to muscular activity or environmental stimulation.
  - This muscle assists with subtle reflexive movements that help protect the body
    from irritants, insects, and sudden tactile sensations. Working alongside adjacent
    cutaneous muscles, it contributes to coordinated skin mobility and communication-related
    body language. Despite its delicate structure, the cervicoscutular muscle supports
    normal skin flexibility and responsiveness.
